# AGENTS.md

## Project Context

- This project uses Claude Code's native agent teams feature
- All project context is in `.claude/` — start with `CLAUDE.md`
- Module docs are in `.claude/modules/`, workflows in `.claude/workflows/`
- Custom subagent definitions are in `.claude/agents/`

## Agent Teams Configuration

- Agent teams enabled via `CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1` (set in `.claude/settings.json`)
- Display mode: auto (configured via `teammateMode` in settings)
- Team lead uses `Shift+Tab` to toggle delegate mode

## Working Conventions

- Follow conventions in `.claude/conventions/`
- Run tests before committing: `[your test command]`
- Run linting before committing: `[your lint command]`

## Teammate Coordination

- Team lead manages the shared task list
- Teammates communicate via mailbox messaging
- Each teammate inherits project context (CLAUDE.md, MCP servers, skills)
- Teammates inherit the lead's permission settings

## Custom Subagents

Available subagent roles (in `.claude/agents/`):
- **researcher** — Codebase exploration and documentation reading
- **implementer** — Code writing, test authoring, file editing
- **reviewer** — Code review, convention checking, validation
- Create new roles: copy `.claude/agents/_template.md`

## Task Quality Gates

- `TeammateIdle` hook runs when a teammate finishes — use for validation
- `TaskCompleted` hook runs when a task is marked complete — exit code 2 prevents completion
- Both hooks can enforce project-specific quality standards
